      "message": "I can\u0027t seem to reproduce this fingerprint, but the schema hasn\u0027t changed (this revision is a \u0027data migration\u0027 which just deletes some rows). With either revision f69cb3 or 26083 I get the same fingerprint.\n\nExample:\n\nMariaDB [(none)]\u003e CREATE DATABASE monasca CHARACTER SET utf8mb4 COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci;\n(monasca-api)[root@operator monasca-api]#monasca_db upgrade\n\u003cSNIP\u003e\nINFO  [alembic.runtime.migration] Running upgrade 8781a256f0c1 -\u003e f69cb3152a76, Remove inhibited and silenced from alarms (Git revision f69cb3152a76e7c586dcc9a03600d1d4ed32c4e6)\n(monasca-api)[root@operator monasca-api]# monasca_db fingerprint\n80f1bab3839430faceb0f99b2b1473204f0c763d\n\nAnd then my change (same hash as expected):\n(monasca-api)[root@operator monasca-api]# alembic -c /monasca-api/monasca_api/db/alembic.ini upgrade head\nINFO  [alembic.runtime.migration] Context impl MySQLImpl.\nINFO  [alembic.runtime.migration] Will assume non-transactional DDL.\nINFO  [alembic.runtime.migration] Running upgrade f69cb3152a76 -\u003e 26083b298bb7, Remove builtin notification types\n(monasca-api)[root@operator monasca-api]# monasca_db fingerprint\n80f1bab3839430faceb0f99b2b1473204f0c763d\n\nExactly how was the database create for these fingerprints? Have I missed something?",
