      "side": 1,
      "message": "No. This is a SHA1 fingerprint of a schema dump as computed here:\n\nhttps://github.com/openstack/monasca-api/blob/0250f81cdcb9e49361f24b52e76e1597a0674739/monasca_api/db/fingerprint.py#L60\n\nGetting it to match the commit ID would pose a bit of a chicken-egg problem :-)\n\nThe bit that _does_ match commit IDs are the values (i.e. revision IDs) in that hash for any legacy revisions (those created by SQL scripts). For these, the commits are in the past so I used the shortened commit IDs as revision identifiers (to make locating the matching SQL script easier).",
